"default": false, "description": "This issue requires a nightly compiler in some way."}, {"id": 2389367932, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMzg5MzY3OTMy", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/F-extern_types", "name": "F-extern_types", "color": "f9c0cc", "default": false, "description": "`#![feature(extern_types)]`"}], "state": "open", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 2, "created_at": "2023-01-07T23:42:59Z", "updated_at": "2023-01-13T07:26:18Z", "closed_at": null, "author_association": "NONE", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "Hello, following code on nightly [playground](https://play.rust-lang.org/?version=nightly&mode=debug&edition=2021&gist=5010620487fdb68eefe1ae7a39fa374a) returns zero, indicating extern type behaving like ZST, while in comparison, `size_of` fails to compile. According to the [RFC](https://rust-lang.github.io/rfcs/1861-extern-types.html), panicking or compilation failure should happen, so this behavior seem incorrect.\r\n\r\n```rust\r\n#![feature(extern_types)]\r\n\r\nextern {\r\n    type Foo;\r\n}\r\n\r\npub fn test() -> usize {\r\n    let ptr: *mut Foo = std::ptr::null_mut();\r\n    unsafe{std::mem::size_of_val::<Foo>(&*ptr)}\r\n}\r\n```\r\n", "closed_by": null, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/106577/reactions", "total_count": 0, "+1": 0, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/106577/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": null}